      "name": "Nominal flow validation at 5 L/min — hemolysis index comparison against FDA benchmark data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against experimental measurements from the FDA generic centrifugal pump benchmark at 5 L/min, 2400 RPM. All hardware operated in nominal condition; no fault states introduced. NIH prediction within 8% of experimental mean across three mesh refinement levels."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-nominal-flow-3lpm",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Nominal flow validation at 3 L/min — hemolysis index comparison",
      "description": "CFD-predicted NIH compared against experimental measurements at 3 L/min, 2000 RPM under nominal hardware conditions. Pump bearings and seals assumed to be in as-new condition throughout the experimental campaign. Agreement within 11% of experimental mean."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-mesh-sensitivity",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh sensitivity study — discretization error quantification",
      "description": "Richardson extrapolation applied across three mesh densities (4M, 8M, 16M cells) at nominal operating point 5 L/min, 2400 RPM. Grid convergence index (GCI) < 2.1% for NIH QoI. All runs performed with nominal geometry; impeller wear and seal degradation not modeled."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-turbulence-model-comparison",
