      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations through benchmark test cases relevant to rotating machinery and viscous flow.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent verified against rotating cavity and lid-driven cavity benchmarks. Published verification reports confirm correct implementation of incompressible Navier-Stokes equations with MRF rotating frame treatment. Code verification level meets MRL 2 threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index for primary QoI (NIH) must be less than 5% at the production mesh density.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation across three mesh levels yields GCI of 2.1% for NIH at the nominal operating point. Discretization error is well-controlled and exceeds MRL 2 requirements. All mesh studies conducted at nominal pump geometry without wear or fault-state geometric perturbations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must be documented with sufficient fidelity to allow direct comparison with CFD boundary conditions, including flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties, and temperature.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental conditions reproduced: bovine blood analog (glycerol-water, viscosity 3.5 mPa·s), flow rates 3–5 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–2400 RPM, temperature 37°C. All experiments conducted on new pump hardware in nominal condition. Sensor calibration records archived. No degraded or fault-state hardware was included in the test matrix."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD-predicted NIH must agree with experimental measurements within 15% across all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "NIH predictions agree within 8–11% of experimental means across five validation operating points. Validation metric satisfies the 15% acceptance criterion. All comparisons made against measurements on nominal hardware; no fault-state experimental data available for comparison."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (NIH, shear stress distribution) must be directly traceable to the clinical acceptance criterion (RH < 1).",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary QoI and is directly related to the relative hemolysis index RH used in the acceptance criterion. Shear stress distribution used as secondary QoI to characterize spatial hemolysis risk. Both QoIs are clinically relevant and traceable to the regulatory decision criterion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must cover the operating envelope (flow rate, speed) relevant to the CPB COU, using geometrically representative pump hardware.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities span the CPB operating envelope (3–5 L/min, 2000–2400 RPM) using the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which is representative of the Class II CPB device family. Validation hardware was in nominal as-new condition throughout; the extended in vivo duty cycle and associated hardware degradation modes encountered in clinical deployment are not represented in the validation campaign."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor scope.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error beyond discretization error is not required to be separately assessed at MRL 2. Residual convergence criteria (< 1e-5 for all equations) documented in simulation reports."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor scope.",
      "rationale": "Formal use error analysis not required at MRL 2. Simulation setup reviewed by a second analyst; boundary condition and material property inputs confirmed against documented experimental conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis damage accumulation model must be justified for the flow regime and QoI relevant to CPB hemolysis prediction.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST turbulence model selected based on published performance for rotating machinery at transitional Reynolds numbers. Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model applied for damage accumulation along Lagrangian particle tracks. Model form consistent with published literature for CFD hemolysis in centrifugal pumps. Model assumes nominal impeller geometry and surface finish; degraded surface conditions due to wear are not represented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) must be traceable to measurements or published reference values with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Pump geometry derived from FDA benchmark CAD files. Fluid properties (density, viscosity) measured at 37°C and documented with calibration records. Inlet/outlet boundary conditions set from experimental flow and pressure measurements. Input uncertainty budget compiled. All inputs reflect nominal hardware and nominal operating conditions; no degraded-state input perturbations (e.g., increased bearing clearance, altered impeller surface roughness due to wear) are included in the input set."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor scope.",
      "rationale": "Statistical characterization of test sample variability not required at MRL 2. Three repeat experiments performed at each operating point to establish measurement repeatability; coefficient of variation < 5% for NIH measurements."
    },
